    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tower-shaped monstrances, having decorative architectural elements such as pinnacles, for displaying the Host (the bread consecrated in the Eucharist) in Christian churches.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
